        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "White platelet syndrome (WPS) is a platelet granule disorder characterized by thrombocytopenia increased mean platelet volumes decreased platelet responsiveness to aggregating agents and significant defects in platelet ultrastructural morphology leading to prolonged bleeding times and bleeding."
